# Implementation Plan - Continuous File Generation

Create a background script `background_generator.py` that generates a new intricate test file in the `timie waste` directory every 60 seconds.

## Proposed Changes

### [New Script]
#### [NEW] [background_generator.py](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/CARAT/timie_waste/background_generator.py)
 - A Python script that runs in an infinite loop (or with a large limit).
 - Every 60 seconds, it picks a random combination of image filters (HOG, GLCM, NLM, CLAHE, etc.) and generates a new [.py](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/CARAT/eval.py) file.
 - Each generated file will follow the pattern `intricate_test_{n}.py`.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
 - Run `python timie_waste/background_generator.py` in the background.
 - Wait 2 minutes and verify that `intricate_test_1.py` and `intricate_test_2.py` have been created.

### Manual Verification
 - Monitor the `timie waste` directory to see the "continuous" growth.
